Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows significantly elevated creatinine, suggesting impaired renal function, and mildly elevated chloride. ALT is raised, indicating possible liver involvement. Triglycerides are slightly above normal. Other parameters, including glucose, electrolytes, proteins, and liver enzymes, are within normal limits. Recommend clinical correlation for renal and hepatic function and consideration of further nephrological and hepatological evaluation.
